  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240ºC/ 220ºC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>chestnut </strong>and <strong>flat white mushrooms </strong>finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1713249697481-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1713249697481-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1713249697481-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1713249697481-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1713249697481-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>shallot</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> with the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong></p><p>Increase the heat to high and cook for 4-5 min or until the mushrooms have softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1713249700110-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1713249700110-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1713249700110-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1713249700110-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1713249700110-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortiglioni</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Tip: It doesn't need to be fully cooked, as it will go in the oven later!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1713249703464-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
